<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="63" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,458,1918]" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,343,1660,1686]" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">Comments:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Deble" authorityYear="2012" box="[372,636,1660,1685]" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Cypella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="magnicristata">
<emphasis box="[372,636,1660,1685]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">Cypella magnicristata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Ravenna (1981 b: 20)" authorityName="Ravenna" authorityPageNumber="20" authorityYear="1981" box="[888,1276,1660,1686]" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Cypella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="armosa">
<emphasis box="[888,1012,1660,1685]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">C. armosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ravenna, P." box="[1021,1276,1660,1686]" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" pagination="15 - 21" refId="ref4520" refString="Ravenna, P. (1981 b) Eight new species in the genus Cypella (Iridaceae). Wrightia 7: 15 - 21." type="journal article" year="1981">Ravenna (1981b: 20)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, both species have large flowers, long and narrowed anthers, and style apice with long adaxial crests. However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Deble" authorityYear="2012" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Cypella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="magnicristata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">C. magnicristata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by the large and obovate outer tepals, the size of inner tepals, and also by the stamens with longer and filiform filaments. The new species also resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Ravenna (1981 a: 492)" authorityName="Ravenna" authorityPageNumber="492" authorityYear="1981" box="[952,1385,1776,1802]" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Cypella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="exilis">
<emphasis box="[952,1113,1776,1801]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">Cypella exilis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ravenna, P." box="[1121,1385,1776,1802]" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" pagination="489 - 492" refId="ref4478" refString="Ravenna, P. (1981 a) A submerged new species of Cypella (Iridaceae), and a new section for the genus (s. str.). Nordic Journal of Botany 1: 489 - 492." type="journal article" year="1981">Ravenna (1981a: 492)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but the latter differs by its smaller and orange flowers, smaller size of outer and inner tepals, and shorter adaxial crests on the style apices. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Deble" authorityYear="2012" box="[457,718,1854,1879]" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Cypella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="magnicristata">
<emphasis box="[457,718,1854,1879]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">Cypella magnicristata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ravenna" authorityYear="1981" box="[1048,1171,1854,1879]" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Cypella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="armosa">
<emphasis box="[1048,1171,1854,1879]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">C. armosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ravenna" authorityYear="1981" box="[1228,1324,1854,1879]" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Cypella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="exilis">
<emphasis box="[1228,1324,1854,1879]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">C. exilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the characters listed in the 
<tableCitation box="[464,554,1892,1918]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="7.[151,239,1355,1379]" captionText="TABLE 2. Comparison of C. magnicristata and its morphologically related species" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">Table 2</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
